# Security Scenarios

A collection of realistic security incidents and model responses demonstrating investigation, containment, remediation, and escalation workflows used in modern IT and security operations.

---

# 🧨 Scenario 1 — Phishing Email Clicked

## 🎯 User Report
> “I clicked a link in an email and entered my password. I think it was fake.”

## 🔍 Investigation
- Check Entra ID sign‑in logs  
- Look for impossible travel  
- Look for unfamiliar IPs  
- Check MFA prompts  
- Review audit logs for mailbox rules  

## 🛑 Containment
1. Reset password  
2. Revoke all sessions  
3. Block malicious domain  
4. Run Defender scan on device  

## 🔧 Remediation
- Remove any malicious inbox rules  
- Confirm no OAuth apps were granted access  
- Educate user on phishing indicators  

## 📝 Ticket Note (Model Answer)
User entered credentials into phishing site. Reset password, revoked sessions, and checked sign‑in logs — no suspicious activity detected. Removed malicious inbox rule and blocked sender domain. Educated user on phishing awareness. Issue contained and resolved.

