# 🔐 Scenario 2 — MFA Fatigue Attack

## 🎯 User Report
> “I keep getting MFA prompts I didn’t request.”

## 🔍 Investigation
- Check sign‑in logs for repeated failures  
- Look for password spray attempts  
- Check risky sign‑ins  

## 🛑 Containment
1. Advise user to deny all prompts  
2. Reset password  
3. Revoke sessions  
4. Check for compromised OAuth apps  

## 🔧 Remediation
- Enforce number matching  
- Review Conditional Access  
- Add additional MFA methods  

## 📝 Ticket Note
User targeted by MFA fatigue attack. Reset password, revoked sessions, and enabled number matching. No suspicious sign‑ins detected after reset. User advised to report future unexpected prompts immediately.

