# 🛡️ Scenario 3 — Suspicious Inbox Rules (BEC Attempt)

## 🎯 User Report
> “Emails are disappearing from my inbox.”

## 🔍 Investigation
- Check mailbox rules  
- Look for “forward to external address”  
- Check audit logs  
- Review sign‑in logs  

## 🛑 Containment
1. Remove malicious rules  
2. Reset password  
3. Revoke sessions  
4. Block external forwarding  

## 🔧 Remediation
- Enable mailbox auditing  
- Review anti‑phishing policies  
- Notify security team  

## 📝 Ticket Note
Detected malicious inbox rule forwarding emails externally. Removed rule, reset password, revoked sessions, and blocked external forwarding. No further suspicious activity observed. Escalated to security team for review.

