# 🖥️ Scenario 4 — Malware Detected by Defender

## 🎯 Alert
> “Microsoft Defender detected: Trojan:Win32/Agent.”

## 🔍 Investigation
- Review Defender alert details  
- Check device timeline  
- Identify source file  
- Check for persistence  

## 🛑 Containment
1. Isolate device in Defender  
2. Block file hash  
3. Block source domain  

## 🔧 Remediation
- Run full scan  
- Remove malware  
- Patch OS and apps  
- Review user permissions  

## 📝 Ticket Note
Defender detected Trojan:Win32/Agent. Device isolated, malware removed, and full scan completed. No persistence mechanisms found. User educated on safe downloading practices.

