# 🧩 Scenario 6 — OAuth App Abuse

## 🎯 Alert
> “User granted high‑risk permissions to unknown app.”

## 🔍 Investigation
- Check app name and publisher  
- Review permissions granted  
- Check audit logs  
- Check sign‑in logs  

## 🛑 Containment
1. Revoke app consent  
2. Reset password  
3. Revoke sessions  

## 🔧 Remediation
- Block app tenant‑wide  
- Enable admin consent workflow  
- Educate user  

## 📝 Ticket Note
User granted OAuth consent to malicious app. Revoked consent, reset password, and blocked app. No data exfiltration detected. Admin consent workflow enabled to prevent recurrence.

